            "subject": "LU-9094 o2iblnd: kill timedout txs from ibp_tx_queue"
          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "James Simmons",
          "email": "uja.ornl@yahoo.com",
          "date": "2017-02-17 15:45:58.000000000",
          "tz": -300
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2017-03-01 05:10:54.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-9019 obd: use 64-bit timestamps for rpc stats",
        "message": "LU-9019 obd: use 64-bit timestamps for rpc stats\n\nThe debugfs rpc stats interface contains timestamps that are\ncomputed from timeval, which overflows in 2038 on 32-bit systems.\n\nThis changes the output to use a timespec64 type to avoid the\noverflow. I also change the format to print the sub-second portion\nas 9 digits (nanoseconds) for clarity, rather than printing six\ndigits without leading zeroes.\n\nChange-Id: I8fca45ef62672f3880a444961cb068d8c436e2c7\nSigned-off-by: James Simmons <uja.ornl@yahoo.com>\nReviewed-on: https://review.whamcloud.com/25410\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Grégoire Pichon <gregoire.pichon@bull.net>\nReviewed-by: Dmitry Eremin <dmitry.eremin@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Oleg Drokin <oleg.drokin@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
